WEBVTT

00:00.510 --> 00:02.317
The Amazon is burning.

00:02.799 --> 00:06.845
A record number of fires over 72,000...

00:07.069 --> 00:10.927
...have been detected in the world's largest rainforest this year.

00:12.252 --> 00:18.939
Brazil's National Institute for Space Research reports that's an 83 percent increase from last year.

00:19.192 --> 00:24.275
Environmental groups say the policies of Brazil's president Jair Bolsonaro...

00:24.539 --> 00:30.374
...encouraged deforestation of the Amazon, which in turn allows for more fires.

00:30.837 --> 00:37.623
Bolsonaro, in turn, alleges that environmental groups started the fires to embarrass his administration.

00:38.303 --> 00:40.854
Meanwhile, the jungle is aflame.

00:41.429 --> 00:46.621
Here, a motorist captures thick smoke pouring into the sky from one of the fires.

00:47.579 --> 00:50.916
The Amazon covers over two million square miles.

00:51.423 --> 00:56.799
It's home to indigenous groups as well as thousands of species of plants and animals.

00:57.109 --> 01:00.633
Two-thirds of the world's plant species can be found there...

01:01.243 --> 01:06.322
...and it's seen as a vital hedge against the carbon emissions that contribute to climate change,...

01:06.621 --> 01:11.491
...a loss that becomes more pressing as global temperatures continue to rise.

